37:48.647 --> 37:50.429
Los Altos de Jalisco is near there. I just glimpsed 
this thing. Well, go ahead, if I find it all. I

37:59.219 --> 38:03.544
thought I had a small picture, which I had glued in 
here years and years ago. But no, he was not

38:03.584 --> 38:07.109
primarily Spanish. I think he was mestizo, 
obviously. And it was quite dark. But

38:15.098 --> 38:16.920
linguistically, fully Spanish. Oh, fluent. And 
he commanded it. As the Spaniards say, he was a

38:21.025 --> 38:24.369
dominio all the way. Spoke it very well. I'm 
curious about the manifestation of prejudice in

38:28.953 --> 38:35.179
Wyoming. Was it something that you sensed very 
greatly as a child? Yes, yes. We were all sent, you

38:38.642 --> 38:41.165
know, we had a Mexican school. Now, this was 
explained, this was geographic, but as quickly as

38:41.665 --> 38:51.055
we got to the fifth grade, you know, we all went to 
the central school. And...

38:54.738 --> 38:55.539
I don't know. I grew up hearing the dirty Mexican 
bit, the greaser. What else were some of the

39:00.387 --> 39:01.509
things? We all carried knives. All the 
stereotypes that you associate with prejudice

39:03.151 --> 39:08.219
were there. And we became very conscious at some 
early age, obviously, because I can remember

39:08.240 --> 39:21.100
being conscious of being Mexican all my life in a 
defensive sense.

39:26.041 --> 39:27.123
I don't know the source. He's the one who put it in. 
Did your family remain Catholic? Oh, yes. I am a bad

39:33.277 --> 39:41.014
one, but I'm

39:33.277 --> 39:41.014
Catholic. You know, it's stuff that a laborer... 
of that vintage wouldn't survive. Church

39:45.423 --> 39:48.286
situation throughout the states of Mexico. In 
other words, he was concerned with things. Yes,

39:51.389 --> 39:52.230
yes. And he was very proud of what the Revolution 
accomplished in the long run. Yeah, yeah. Did he

39:57.495 --> 39:59.417
ever think of going back to Mexico? No. He

40:01.439 --> 40:10.948
talked of going away from Wyoming, but he said he'd 
like to live in Ogden, Utah, or Stockton,

40:11.468 --> 40:21.139
California, or Portland, Oregon, each of these 
towns he had lived in in his younger days when he was

40:11.468 --> 40:21.139
with the railroad or something like this. But 
never talked about going back to Mexico. And I

40:24.602 --> 40:38.978
think that a great deal of the hesitancy that my 
family has in owning up to their Mexitanness comes

40:24.602 --> 40:38.978
from this instilling at a very early age on the part 
of my mother more than my father. somehow a reserve

40:39.093 --> 40:43.100
against Mexico, even though he's very proud of 
what they've done. He never said, I want to go back

40:43.120 --> 40:46.485
to visit. I don't believe it. He would fantasize 
about the food and the fruits they would have. But

40:51.594 --> 40:56.983
never going back for a visit, nor to live. Which 
leads me to believe that maybe he did have a family

40:57.385 --> 41:04.355
back then, you know, and would be reluctant to go 
back for that reason. Because he didn't, as far as

41:04.375 --> 41:09.923
you know, have the same kind of traumatic 
experience that your mother is a 13-year-old.

41:10.263 --> 41:12.947
It's easy to see how she would have that. Well, you 
see, at the time of the Revolution, he would

41:12.967 --> 41:16.492
already have been a young man. I suppose a man, 
given the standards of that age, he would have

41:16.532 --> 41:19.596
been... If you take 1910 as the starting point. He 
was younger than his brother, who was with Villa.

41:27.404 --> 41:31.348
And that's what would perhaps put him into this 
kind of camp following situation. I've deduced

41:32.409 --> 41:42.921
this for myself, both from my recollections and 
from what my cousins told me

41:32.409 --> 41:42.921
about him. It's very intriguing, and I don't want 
to pursue it much more, because I'm sure the truth

41:42.941 --> 41:49.127
isn't going to be as nice as my imagination. But I 
tried to give you a factual account of what I

41:49.715 --> 41:58.186
remember and not make them heroes of the 
revolution or anything like that. You talked

41:58.266 --> 42:04.334
about how you have not been to Mexico except 
Juarez.

42:04.994 --> 42:06.136
But you did live in South America. Yes, I lived in 
Lima. I was a Fulbright professor at the Catholic

42:07.177 --> 42:12.224
University in 1967. How did you feel about Peru? 
